translate ru strings:

    old "Waking to the first beams of the morning sun, Sarah stumbled awake."
    new "Waking to the first beams of the morning sun, Sarah stumbled awake."

    old "She felt as though she had been woken from a dream. A dream that now rapidly receded from her memory."
    new "She felt as though she had been woken from a dream. A dream that now rapidly receded from her memory."

    old "For a moment, she reached around, finding her footing."
    new "For a moment, she reached around, finding her footing."

    old "The ruins of a home."
    new "The ruins of a home."

    old "She remembered how she had ended up here, and now the pain in her back was reminding her why she really shouldn't be sleeping on the floor."
    new "She remembered how she had ended up here, and now the pain in her back was reminding her why she really shouldn't be sleeping on the floor."

    old "Stretching, Sarah felt her limbs crack and the pain pull away from her."
    new "Stretching, Sarah felt her limbs crack and the pain pull away from her."

    old "Climbing out of the ruins and back onto the road, Sarah began to make her way back to the camp."
    new "Climbing out of the ruins and back onto the road, Sarah began to make her way back to the camp."

    old "Already, there was a good bustle of activity. Mythran soldiers. Mercenaries. Soldiers bonded quickly."
    new "Already, there was a good bustle of activity. Mythran soldiers. Mercenaries. Soldiers bonded quickly."

    old "Walking up the street, Sarah saluted a few small units that were headed towards the city gates, setting up defenses."
    new "Walking up the street, Sarah saluted a few small units that were headed towards the city gates, setting up defenses."

    old "Suddenly, she saw a figure rush up towards her."
    new "Suddenly, she saw a figure rush up towards her."

    old "Sarah waved at Kate as she came closer."
    new "Sarah waved at Kate as she came closer."

    old "I was looking all over for you last night."
    new "I was looking all over for you last night."

    old "Looks like you had a good night."
    new "Looks like you had a good night."

    old "My back is all fucked up."
    new "My back is all fucked up."

    old "That good huh?"
    new "That good huh?"

    old "You're getting to old for stuff like that, Sarah."
    new "You're getting to old for stuff like that, Sarah."

    old "Old? I'm not even thirty."
    new "Old? I'm not even thirty."

    old "Well, you gotta count those princess days as double. Easy living weakens the bones."
    new "Well, you gotta count those princess days as double. Easy living weakens the bones."

    old "I don't think it works that way."
    new "I don't think it works that way."

    old "The two of them continued walking towards the camp."
    new "The two of them continued walking towards the camp."

    old "Anyway, shouldn't you be...I don't really know what you should be doing."
    new "Anyway, shouldn't you be...I don't really know what you should be doing."

    old "Guarding the south gate? Yeah, they needed twenty hands so I send half my unit there, but there really isn't much more to do than that."
    new "Guarding the south gate? Yeah, they needed twenty hands so I send half my unit there, but there really isn't much more to do than that."

    old "If you're asking me, I don't even really know why the Mythrans need us here."
    new "If you're asking me, I don't even really know why the Mythrans need us here."

    old "Sarah knew some of the other reasons why they had been called out here, but she didn't want to trouble Kate with such things."
    new "Sarah knew some of the other reasons why they had been called out here, but she didn't want to trouble Kate with such things."

    old "She decided to change the subject."
    new "She decided to change the subject."

    old "So, I guess if you don't have anything else to do, you're free to help me out."
    new "So, I guess if you don't have anything else to do, you're free to help me out."

    old "What do you need a hand with?"
    new "What do you need a hand with?"

    old "Well it's been a while since I've drawn my sword, and it's getting rusty."
    new "Well it's been a while since I've drawn my sword, and it's getting rusty."

    old "She saw a smile grow on Kate's face."
    new "She saw a smile grow on Kate's face."

    old "You wanna spar? Fuck me, it's been a while. What was the score again, twenty-three against nineteen, my way?"
    new "You wanna spar? Fuck me, it's been a while. What was the score again, twenty-three against nineteen, my way?"

    old "That's not how I recall it. Wasn't it the other way around?"
    new "That's not how I recall it. Wasn't it the other way around?"

    old "Making their way towards a cleared out space that functioned as a staging ground, the two women began to prepare themselves."
    new "Making their way towards a cleared out space that functioned as a staging ground, the two women began to prepare themselves."

    old "Well, tell you what. I'm gonna beat you so hard you're gonna be begging me to stop keepin score."
    new "Well, tell you what. I'm gonna beat you so hard you're gonna be begging me to stop keepin score."

    old "Sarah pulled out one of the training swords from a crate. She grabbed another and threw it at Kate."
    new "Sarah pulled out one of the training swords from a crate. She grabbed another and threw it at Kate."

    old "Effortlessly, Kate caught it in midair."
    new "Effortlessly, Kate caught it in midair."

    old "Training swords? Really?"
    new "Training swords? Really?"

    old "Spinning the blade around in her hand, Kate got into position."
    new "Spinning the blade around in her hand, Kate got into position."

    old "Sarah entered her own stance, raising the dulled training blade in front of her."
    new "Sarah entered her own stance, raising the dulled training blade in front of her."

    old "Of course training swords. I don't wanna put you into the medic tent."
    new "Of course training swords. I don't wanna put you into the medic tent."

    old "Promise me, if I have to go to what we call a medic tent, just do me a favor and put me out of my misery."
    new "Promise me, if I have to go to what we call a medic tent, just do me a favor and put me out of my misery."

    old "Our camp doctor is like ninty years old and blind as a bat."
    new "Our camp doctor is like ninty years old and blind as a bat."

    old "Send him my regards when I drop you off there."
    new "Send him my regards when I drop you off there."

    old "Instantly, each of the two women recognized the moment."
    new "Instantly, each of the two women recognized the moment."

    old "Lunging forward, each closing the distance, their bodies rushed up towards one another and their blades clashed."
    new "Lunging forward, each closing the distance, their bodies rushed up towards one another and their blades clashed."

    old "Once the difference between herself and Kate had been astronomical, but over the years they had become more equally matched."
    new "Once the difference between herself and Kate had been astronomical, but over the years they had become more equally matched."

    old "Stepping back to create space, Sarah swung her blade, but Kate dove down underneath the blade."
    new "Stepping back to create space, Sarah swung her blade, but Kate dove down underneath the blade."

    old "Though the two of them were closely matched, their styles could not be more different."
    new "Though the two of them were closely matched, their styles could not be more different."

    old "Sarah held the upper hand when it came to raw physical strength, but Kate was faster than her."
    new "Sarah held the upper hand when it came to raw physical strength, but Kate was faster than her."

    old "It was exactly that advantage that Kate was now trying to play into, leaping forward again as she swiped the blade at Sarah's legs."
    new "It was exactly that advantage that Kate was now trying to play into, leaping forward again as she swiped the blade at Sarah's legs."

    old "More than once, Sarah had lost to Kate on account of this trick."
    new "More than once, Sarah had lost to Kate on account of this trick."

    old "But experience had made her wise, and Sarah effortlessly stepped over the sweeping blade."
    new "But experience had made her wise, and Sarah effortlessly stepped over the sweeping blade."

    old "Swiftly raising her knee, she brought it cracking against Kate's lower jaw."
    new "Swiftly raising her knee, she brought it cracking against Kate's lower jaw."

    old "Sarah watched the dust blow up across the arena as Kate rolled across the ground."
    new "Sarah watched the dust blow up across the arena as Kate rolled across the ground."

    old "She took a step forward, but seeing Kate recover and crawl back onto her feet, Sarah halted."
    new "She took a step forward, but seeing Kate recover and crawl back onto her feet, Sarah halted."

    old "Kate louded gathered the phlegm in her mouth and spat it out."
    new "Kate louded gathered the phlegm in her mouth and spat it out."

    old "Sarah saw the red traces of blood mixed in with the spit."
    new "Sarah saw the red traces of blood mixed in with the spit."

    old "You alright?"
    new "You alright?"

    old "Lucky shot is all. I'm just holding back cause I don't wanna fuck up your pretty face."
    new "Lucky shot is all. I'm just holding back cause I don't wanna fuck up your pretty face."

    old "Well, that's why I don't have to hold back from your face."
    new "Well, that's why I don't have to hold back from your face."

    old "Funny."
    new "Funny."

    old "Kate leapt forward."
    new "Kate leapt forward."

    old "Sarah had expected the same trick, but this time, Kate came for her head on."
    new "Sarah had expected the same trick, but this time, Kate came for her head on."

    old "Kate thrusted her blade directly at Sarah, and only a moment before it connected did she managed to swipe it aside."
    new "Kate thrusted her blade directly at Sarah, and only a moment before it connected did she managed to swipe it aside."

    old "But rather than retreat, Sarah saw Kate twist her body into her."
    new "But rather than retreat, Sarah saw Kate twist her body into her."

    old "Kate's shoulder connected with her own chest and Sarah felt the air knocked from her lungs."
    new "Kate's shoulder connected with her own chest and Sarah felt the air knocked from her lungs."

    old "Stumbling backwards, Sarah felt her balance slip, crashing hard against the sandy ground."
    new "Stumbling backwards, Sarah felt her balance slip, crashing hard against the sandy ground."

    old "As dust rose up all around her, blinding her vision, Sarah scrambled to find her footing."
    new "As dust rose up all around her, blinding her vision, Sarah scrambled to find her footing."

    old "In the midsts of the melee, she saw Kate's feet moving, drawing nearer to her."
    new "In the midsts of the melee, she saw Kate's feet moving, drawing nearer to her."

    old "Sarah threw up her sword, catching Kate's training blade just a moment before it connected with her."
    new "Sarah threw up her sword, catching Kate's training blade just a moment before it connected with her."

    old "Training blades were dull, but solid enough to inflict a real beating."
    new "Training blades were dull, but solid enough to inflict a real beating."

    old "The sound of the swords connecting rang out across the training ground."
    new "The sound of the swords connecting rang out across the training ground."

    old "Sarah gathered all her strength, rising up from bended knee she pushed Kate's blade back."
    new "Sarah gathered all her strength, rising up from bended knee she pushed Kate's blade back."

    old "Delivering a quick punch into Kate's unguarded side."
    new "Delivering a quick punch into Kate's unguarded side."

    old "She saw Kate stumble backwards. Enough to teach her a lesson. Not enough to win the fight."
    new "She saw Kate stumble backwards. Enough to teach her a lesson. Not enough to win the fight."

    old "Kate resumed her stance."
    new "Kate resumed her stance."

    old "Kate was not going to let up, she was keeping the pressure on her."
    new "Kate was not going to let up, she was keeping the pressure on her."

    old "Meet Kate head-on"
    new "Meet Kate head-on"

    old "Sarah knew where her advantage laid."
    new "Sarah knew where her advantage laid."

    old "Kate was losing sight of her own strengths, instead hoping to overpower Sarah."
    new "Kate was losing sight of her own strengths, instead hoping to overpower Sarah."

    old "She didn't stand a chance."
    new "She didn't stand a chance."

    old "Sarah digged her heels into the sand as she took her stance."
    new "Sarah digged her heels into the sand as she took her stance."

    old "Kate rushed up towards her, just as Sarah had expected."
    new "Kate rushed up towards her, just as Sarah had expected."

    old "Kate brought her sword down on Sarah like a rain of iron."
    new "Kate brought her sword down on Sarah like a rain of iron."

    old "But Sarah held her stance, giving not an inch and meeting each blow with her own counter."
    new "But Sarah held her stance, giving not an inch and meeting each blow with her own counter."

    old "It wasn't long before Kate extended herself too far, the rhythm of her attacks slowing."
    new "It wasn't long before Kate extended herself too far, the rhythm of her attacks slowing."

    old "And then, Sarah turned the fight."
    new "And then, Sarah turned the fight."

    old "Driving her leg forward, she got in close to Kate, inside of her sword arm's reach."
    new "Driving her leg forward, she got in close to Kate, inside of her sword arm's reach."

    old "Sarah spun her blade and drove the handle into Kate's hip."
    new "Sarah spun her blade and drove the handle into Kate's hip."

    old "With each blow, Sarah could see Kate stepping, moving, trying to create distance, but Sarah would not allow it."
    new "With each blow, Sarah could see Kate stepping, moving, trying to create distance, but Sarah would not allow it."

    old "By now, it was Sarah who was swinging her sword and Kate desperately trying to parry her."
    new "By now, it was Sarah who was swinging her sword and Kate desperately trying to parry her."

    old "Yet, unlike Sarah, Kate did tire."
    new "Yet, unlike Sarah, Kate did tire."

    old "Each swing, each blow, drained more and more of her stamina."
    new "Each swing, each blow, drained more and more of her stamina."

    old "Sarah swung her blade overhead and brought it down."
    new "Sarah swung her blade overhead and brought it down."

    old "As if she was hammering a stake into the ground, Sarah brought her sword down like a hammer."
    new "As if she was hammering a stake into the ground, Sarah brought her sword down like a hammer."

    old "And each blow, Kate blocked or parried..."
    new "And each blow, Kate blocked or parried..."

    old "Until she didn't."
    new "Until she didn't."

    old "When her arm tired, and she was a moment too slow, Sarah's heavy swing broke through her defense and the dulled training blade struck Kate in the shoulder."
    new "When her arm tired, and she was a moment too slow, Sarah's heavy swing broke through her defense and the dulled training blade struck Kate in the shoulder."

    old "Instantly Kate's legs buckled and she collapsed to her knees."
    new "Instantly Kate's legs buckled and she collapsed to her knees."

    old "Sarah reached down, grabbing Kate by the hair, twisting her head and putting the tip of her training sword up against Kate's throat."
    new "Sarah reached down, grabbing Kate by the hair, twisting her head and putting the tip of her training sword up against Kate's throat."

    old "Do you yield?"
    new "Do you yield?"

    old "Kate dropped her sword and threw up her hands."
    new "Kate dropped her sword and threw up her hands."

    old "I give up. You win."
    new "I give up. You win."

    old "Sarah lowered her sword and let her grip on Kate slip."
    new "Sarah lowered her sword and let her grip on Kate slip."

    old "She reached down with her hand, offering it to Kate, which she gratefully took."
    new "She reached down with her hand, offering it to Kate, which she gratefully took."

    old "She pulled Kate back onto her feet."
    new "She pulled Kate back onto her feet."

    old "Fuck me."
    new "Fuck me."

    old "Kate was almost out of breath."
    new "Kate was almost out of breath."

    old "When did you become so freaking strong?"
    new "When did you become so freaking strong?"

    old "Practice makes perfect, I guess."
    new "Practice makes perfect, I guess."

    old "Kate scoffed."
    new "Kate scoffed."

    old "Yeah, practice and never starving when you grow up."
    new "Yeah, practice and never starving when you grow up."

    old "Ooh please, you're gonna blame it on that?"
    new "Ooh please, you're gonna blame it on that?"

    old "Well, the alternative is that I blame it on myself, and that ain't happening."
    new "Well, the alternative is that I blame it on myself, and that ain't happening."

    old "Try to outmanoeuvre her"
    new "Try to outmanoeuvre her"

    old "Kate was going to keep coming for her, she'd have to try and be faster than her."
    new "Kate was going to keep coming for her, she'd have to try and be faster than her."

    old "As Kate thrusted her blade forward against, Sarah stepped aside."
    new "As Kate thrusted her blade forward against, Sarah stepped aside."

    old "The first attack she managed to dodge."
    new "The first attack she managed to dodge."

    old "The next she parried."
    new "The next she parried."

    old "But each attack followed faster on the other, and before she knew it Sarah lost track."
    new "But each attack followed faster on the other, and before she knew it Sarah lost track."

    old "Left. Right. Up. A swipe at her feet."
    new "Left. Right. Up. A swipe at her feet."

    old "Kate improvised and moved with a speed that was impossible for Sarah to follow."
    new "Kate improvised and moved with a speed that was impossible for Sarah to follow."

    old "When she tried to side-step another attack, it was too late that Sarah realized Kate had predicted it."
    new "When she tried to side-step another attack, it was too late that Sarah realized Kate had predicted it."

    old "Sarah could hear the air being cut, so swift did Kate's blade drive into her ankle."
    new "Sarah could hear the air being cut, so swift did Kate's blade drive into her ankle."

    old "Her balance lost, Sarah stumbled and tried to recover, but the weight of her armor dragged her to the earth."
    new "Her balance lost, Sarah stumbled and tried to recover, but the weight of her armor dragged her to the earth."

    old "Clattering, stumbling, again Sarah tried to find her balance back, but this time she knew it was too late."
    new "Clattering, stumbling, again Sarah tried to find her balance back, but this time she knew it was too late."

    old "She felt Kate's feet drive into her stomach."
    new "She felt Kate's feet drive into her stomach."

    old "Instinctively, Sarah started to cough and reach for her stomach, her blade slipping away from her."
    new "Instinctively, Sarah started to cough and reach for her stomach, her blade slipping away from her."

    old "Rolling onto her back, she felt herself suddenly pinned."
    new "Rolling onto her back, she felt herself suddenly pinned."

    old "When she finally opened her eyes again, she looked up and saw Kate standing over her, her feet planted firmly on her chest."
    new "When she finally opened her eyes again, she looked up and saw Kate standing over her, her feet planted firmly on her chest."

    old "Kate casually held the training sword at her neck."
    new "Kate casually held the training sword at her neck."

    old "She didn't need to, it was obvious that she had won."
    new "She didn't need to, it was obvious that she had won."

    old "Kate just smiled at her."
    new "Kate just smiled at her."

    old "Are you going to take your foot off me?"
    new "Are you going to take your foot off me?"

    old "Sorry. I just like seeing you on your back."
    new "Sorry. I just like seeing you on your back."

    old "Sarah pushed her foot off her chest."
    new "Sarah pushed her foot off her chest."

    old "Like a good sport, she found Kate's hand extended down to her. Eagerly, she grabbed it and allowed herself to be pulled back onto her feet."
    new "Like a good sport, she found Kate's hand extended down to her. Eagerly, she grabbed it and allowed herself to be pulled back onto her feet."

    old "Guess I still got plenty to learn."
    new "Guess I still got plenty to learn."

    old "Don't go too hard on yourself. I've been at this a lot longer than you have."
    new "Don't go too hard on yourself. I've been at this a lot longer than you have."

    old "So you mean that in a few years I'll be winning?"
    new "So you mean that in a few years I'll be winning?"

    old "Easy now."
    new "Easy now."

    old "The sound of clapping hands rang out across the sparring field."
    new "The sound of clapping hands rang out across the sparring field."

    old "The two women each turned their head simultaneously towards the sound."
    new "The two women each turned their head simultaneously towards the sound."

    old "Sitting on a block of wood, near the edge, was Cassius."
    new "Sitting on a block of wood, near the edge, was Cassius."

    old "A very admirable showing."
    new "A very admirable showing."

    old "Instantly, Sarah saw Kate step passed her."
    new "Instantly, Sarah saw Kate step passed her."

    old "And who the fuck are you?"
    new "And who the fuck are you?"

    old "Sarah put her hand on Kate's arm."
    new "Sarah put her hand on Kate's arm."

    old "His name is Cassius. A slave."
    new "His name is Cassius. A slave."

    old "Kate spat in the sand. More blood."
    new "Kate spat in the sand. More blood."

    old "I ain't no fucking Mythran, and I'll be damned if I adress anyone as a slave."
    new "I ain't no fucking Mythran, and I'll be damned if I adress anyone as a slave."

    old "Sarah instantly felt guilty for having done so."
    new "Sarah instantly felt guilty for having done so."

    old "Cassius, for his part, only smiled and casually strode across the training field."
    new "Cassius, for his part, only smiled and casually strode across the training field."

    old "A rock is a rock. A river a river. And a slave a slave."
    new "A rock is a rock. A river a river. And a slave a slave."

    old "To spend time worrying about one's own nature, what a waste."
    new "To spend time worrying about one's own nature, what a waste."

    old "Sarah could see Kate frown."
    new "Sarah could see Kate frown."

    old "Whatever, I still ain't callin you a slave. What else are you?"
    new "Whatever, I still ain't callin you a slave. What else are you?"

    old "Cassius. First among equals. War-Brother to Dio."
    new "Cassius. First among equals. War-Brother to Dio."

    old "Yeah, whatever. Is that like a fancy way of saying soldier in Mythran?"
    new "Yeah, whatever. Is that like a fancy way of saying soldier in Mythran?"

    old "Cassius continued to smile as he always did, as if nothing mattered or bothered."
    new "Cassius continued to smile as he always did, as if nothing mattered or bothered."

    old "I suppose that's close enough."
    new "I suppose that's close enough."

    old "And you had something to say about that show back there?"
    new "And you had something to say about that show back there?"

    old "He nodded, suddenly stern."
    new "He nodded, suddenly stern."

    old "Cassius turned to Kate."
    new "Cassius turned to Kate."

    old "You allowed her to lure you into her own style."
    new "You allowed her to lure you into her own style."

    old "You must have known that physically you were no match for her."
    new "You must have known that physically you were no match for her."

    old "Kate's face turned sour."
    new "Kate's face turned sour."

    old "Tell you what, pretty-boy, I ain't looking for a coach."
    new "Tell you what, pretty-boy, I ain't looking for a coach."

    old "Cassius bowed his head gracefully."
    new "Cassius bowed his head gracefully."

    old "I only sought to be of service."
    new "I only sought to be of service."

    old "Well, go bother someone who gives a damn, alright?"
    new "Well, go bother someone who gives a damn, alright?"

    old "Cause if you wanna teach me anything, we can go a few rounds some other time and I'll show you what I know."
    new "Cause if you wanna teach me anything, we can go a few rounds some other time and I'll show you what I know."

    old "I'll consider that a promise."
    new "I'll consider that a promise."

    old "Cassius turned to Sarah."
    new "Cassius turned to Sarah."

    old "You must have known you were no match for her speed."
    new "You must have known you were no match for her speed."

    old "Sarah nodded. She knew she'd made a mistake."
    new "Sarah nodded. She knew she'd made a mistake."

    old "Yeah, you're right. But in the middle of a fight, it can be hard to stay focussed."
    new "Yeah, you're right. But in the middle of a fight, it can be hard to stay focussed."

    old "True, but that is when we need our faculties most."
    new "True, but that is when we need our faculties most."

    old "Thank you for the kind advice."
    new "Thank you for the kind advice."

    old "I live to serve."
    new "I live to serve."

    old "What are you doing here, anyway?"
    new "What are you doing here, anyway?"

    old "Cassius continued, not breaking a beat."
    new "Cassius continued, not breaking a beat."

    old "I've come to extend an invitation to Sarah. And friends, of course."
    new "I've come to extend an invitation to Sarah. And friends, of course."

    old "I told my War-Sister, Dio about meeting you, and she insisted that I invite you to break bread with us tonight."
    new "I told my War-Sister, Dio about meeting you, and she insisted that I invite you to break bread with us tonight."

    old "It will be in the slave quarter, so I fear the usual luxuries might be absent."
    new "It will be in the slave quarter, so I fear the usual luxuries might be absent."

    old "But I promise you will be well entertained."
    new "But I promise you will be well entertained."

    old "He gestured towards Kate."
    new "He gestured towards Kate."

    old "And your friend is more than welcome, or any other friends you might have."
    new "And your friend is more than welcome, or any other friends you might have."

    old "Accept Cassius' invitation"
    new "Accept Cassius' invitation"

    old "I think we'd be honored to accept your invitation. Please tell your sister we will attend."
    new "I think we'd be honored to accept your invitation. Please tell your sister we will attend."

    old "We?"
    new "We?"

    old "Sarah elbowed Kate."
    new "Sarah elbowed Kate."

    old "Aah, yes, of course. We're honored."
    new "Aah, yes, of course. We're honored."

    old "Cassius' steel gaze broke into a wide smile."
    new "Cassius' steel gaze broke into a wide smile."

    old "My sister will be delighted to hear!"
    new "My sister will be delighted to hear!"

    old "Reject his invitation"
    new "Reject his invitation"

    old "Your offer is very kind, but I fear I'm already very busy."
    new "Your offer is very kind, but I fear I'm already very busy."

    old "He regarded her for a moment, then his harsh expresion broke and gave way to his usual casual attitude."
    new "He regarded her for a moment, then his harsh expresion broke and gave way to his usual casual attitude."

    old "Of course, I will report your answer back to my sister."
    new "Of course, I will report your answer back to my sister."

    old "I fear she will be heartbroken."
    new "I fear she will be heartbroken."

    old "Give her my condolences."
    new "Give her my condolences."

    old "Cassius bowed."
    new "Cassius bowed."

    old "Well, I feel that I have taken up enough of your time."
    new "Well, I feel that I have taken up enough of your time."

    old "Cassius bowed, turned, and walked away."
    new "Cassius bowed, turned, and walked away."

    old "Watching him leave, Sarah found Kate looking at her."
    new "Watching him leave, Sarah found Kate looking at her."

    old "Am I really going to have to spend a whole night in some slum eating stale bread because of you?"
    new "Am I really going to have to spend a whole night in some slum eating stale bread because of you?"

    old "Ooh, I thougt you didn't want to treat him like a slave."
    new "Ooh, I thougt you didn't want to treat him like a slave."

    old "That doesn't mean I wanna eat rancid food."
    new "That doesn't mean I wanna eat rancid food."

    old "Maybe you shouldn't have been so mean to him."
    new "Maybe you shouldn't have been so mean to him."

    old "Mean? You're the one who was giving him trouble."
    new "Mean? You're the one who was giving him trouble."

    old "Well yeah, but that's just my winning personality. You're the one who turned down an invitation. That's cold."
    new "Well yeah, but that's just my winning personality. You're the one who turned down an invitation. That's cold."

    old "Well, it doesn't matter. I have enough on my mind, I don't need to be getting dragged into whatever that was about."
